zhoneDsl_MIB.description: The MIB module to describe the Zhone specific implementation of HDSL, HDSL2, SDSL and G.SHDSL

zhoneDslLineTable.name: zhoneDslLineTable
zhoneDslLineTable.description: This table contains common attributes describing DSL physical line interfaces for DSLs without a MIB standard.

zhoneDslLineEntry.name: zhoneDslLineEntry
zhoneDslLineEntry.description: An entry in the zhoneDslLine Table.

zhoneDslLineType.name: zhoneDslLineType
zhoneDslLineType.description: The DSL type. Many modem vendors allow software selection between HDSL, HDSL2, SDSL and SHDSL. Using zhoneDslLineTypeSupported the user can see what dsl option is available on this interface.

zhoneDslLineCapabilities.name: zhoneDslLineCapabilities
zhoneDslLineCapabilities.description: The DSL types supported on this interface. This is a bit-map of possible types. This variable can be used to determine zhoneDslLineType.

zhoneDslLineStatus.name: zhoneDslLineStatus
zhoneDslLineStatus.description: The DSL modem status. Detailed modem state maybe available in the status table.

zhoneDslUpLineRate.name: zhoneDslUpLineRate
zhoneDslUpLineRate.description: The DSL upstream (cpe->co) line rate on this interface.

zhoneDslDownLineRate.name: zhoneDslDownLineRate
zhoneDslDownLineRate.description: The DSL downstream (co->cpe) line rate on this interface.

zhoneDslLineConfigProfile.name: zhoneDslLineConfigProfile
zhoneDslLineConfigProfile.description: The value of this object identifies the row in the respective dsl configuration profile table. (Ex: if zhoneDslLineType is HDSL2, then the profile identifies an HDSL2 configuration profile.) It is assumed that all profile names are unique to the system. In the case which the configuration profile has not been set, the value will be set to `ZhoneDefault'. This is a profile (by type) which will be persisted and then able to be modified by a management station in order to modify the DEFAULT values.

zhoneDslLineAlarmProfile.name: zhoneDslLineAlarmProfile
zhoneDslLineAlarmProfile.description: The value of this object identifies the row in the respective dsl alarm profile table. (Ex: if zhoneDslLineType is HDSL2 then the profile identifies an HDSL2 alarm profile.) It is assumed that all profile names are unique to the system. In the case where the configuration profile has not been set, the value will be set to `ZhoneDefault'.

zhoneDslLineRowStatus.name: zhoneDslLineRowStatus
zhoneDslLineRowStatus.description: Row status in order to add an entry in this table. The required fields to be added are: (ARE ALL THE DEFAULTS OKAY)

zhoneHdsl2ConfigProfileTable.name: zhoneHdsl2ConfigProfileTable
zhoneHdsl2ConfigProfileTable.description: This table contains information for HDSL2 configuration.

zhoneHdsl2ConfigProfileEntry.name: zhoneHdsl2ConfigProfileEntry
zhoneHdsl2ConfigProfileEntry.description: An entry in the zhoneHdsl2ConfigProfile Table.

zhoneHdsl2ConfigProfileName.name: zhoneHdsl2ConfigProfileName
zhoneHdsl2ConfigProfileName.description: Configuration profile name. Used by the zhoneHdsl2LineConfigProfile entry to map zhoneDslLine Entry to the appropriate profile. When `dynamic' profiles are implemented, the profile name is user specified. Also, the system will always provide a default profile whose name is `DEFVAL'. When `static' profiles are implemented, there is an one-to-one relationship between each line and its profile. In which case, the profile name will need to algorithmically represent the Line's ifIndex. Therefore, the profile's name is a decimal zed string of the ifIndex that is fixed-length (i.e., 10) with leading zero(s). For example, the profile name for ifIndex which equals '15' will be '0000000015'.

zhoneHdsl2ConfigUnitMode.name: zhoneHdsl2ConfigUnitMode
zhoneHdsl2ConfigUnitMode.description: Unit is configured as the CO(central office)or CPE (customer premise)side.

zhoneHdsl2ConfigTransmitPowerbackoffMode.name: zhoneHdsl2ConfigTransmitPowerbackoffMode
zhoneHdsl2ConfigTransmitPowerbackoffMode.description: Determines if the transmit power backoff defined in HDSL2 standard is used.

zhoneHdsl2ConfigDecoderCoeffA.name: zhoneHdsl2ConfigDecoderCoeffA
zhoneHdsl2ConfigDecoderCoeffA.description: 21 bit value corresponding to the decoder coefficient A. The default is the ANSI HDSL2 default.

zhoneHdsl2ConfigDecoderCoeffB.name: zhoneHdsl2ConfigDecoderCoeffB
zhoneHdsl2ConfigDecoderCoeffB.description: 21 bit value corresponding to the decoder coefficient A. The default is the ANSI HDSL2 default.

zhoneHdsl2ConfigFrameSyncWord.name: zhoneHdsl2ConfigFrameSyncWord
zhoneHdsl2ConfigFrameSyncWord.description: 10 bit frame sync word. The default is the HDSL2 standard.

zhoneHdsl2ConfigStuffBits.name: zhoneHdsl2ConfigStuffBits
zhoneHdsl2ConfigStuffBits.description: 4 bit stuff pattern. The default is the HDSL2 standard.

zhoneHdsl2ConfigRowStatus.name: zhoneHdsl2ConfigRowStatus
zhoneHdsl2ConfigRowStatus.description: Status in order to create/delete rows. For creation the following fields are required:

zhoneHdsl2StatusTable.name: zhoneHdsl2StatusTable
zhoneHdsl2StatusTable.description: This table contains HDSL2 specific line status information. An entry into this table is automatically created whenever a zhoneDslLineEntry is created and the type is HDSL2.

zhoneHdsl2StatusEntry.name: zhoneHdsl2StatusEntry
zhoneHdsl2StatusEntry.description: An entry in the zhoneHdsl2Status Table.

zhoneHdsl2DriftAlarm.name: zhoneHdsl2DriftAlarm
zhoneHdsl2DriftAlarm.description: Indicates that the framer automatically attempted to adjust for clock drift. This is not applicable for ATM.

zhoneHdsl2FramerIBStatus.name: zhoneHdsl2FramerIBStatus
zhoneHdsl2FramerIBStatus.description: Returns the segd,sega,uib and losd bits. The format of the octet is: x x x x segd sega uib losd.

zhoneHdsl2LocalPSDMaskStatus.name: zhoneHdsl2LocalPSDMaskStatus
zhoneHdsl2LocalPSDMaskStatus.description: Returns a number corresponding to the transmit power backoff requested by the local unit.

zhoneHdsl2LoopAttenuation.name: zhoneHdsl2LoopAttenuation
zhoneHdsl2LoopAttenuation.description: Estimation of the loop attenuation in tenths of a DB. by the local unit.

zhoneHdsl2RmtPSDMaskStatus.name: zhoneHdsl2RmtPSDMaskStatus
zhoneHdsl2RmtPSDMaskStatus.description: Returns a number corresponding to the transmit power backoff requested by the remote unit.

zhoneHdsl2RmtCountryCode.name: zhoneHdsl2RmtCountryCode
zhoneHdsl2RmtCountryCode.description: ANSI HDSL2 Country code of the remote unit.

zhoneHdsl2RmtVersion.name: zhoneHdsl2RmtVersion
zhoneHdsl2RmtVersion.description: HDSL2 version of the remote unit.

zhoneHdsl2RmtProviderCode.name: zhoneHdsl2RmtProviderCode
zhoneHdsl2RmtProviderCode.description: Provider word of the remote unit.

zhoneHdsl2RmtTxEncoderA.name: zhoneHdsl2RmtTxEncoderA
zhoneHdsl2RmtTxEncoderA.description: The remote unit's 21 bit encoder coefficient A

zhoneHdsl2RmtTxEncoderB.name: zhoneHdsl2RmtTxEncoderB
zhoneHdsl2RmtTxEncoderB.description: The remote unit's 21 bit encoder coefficient B

zhoneHdsl2TipRingStatus.name: zhoneHdsl2TipRingStatus
zhoneHdsl2TipRingStatus.description: Indicates whether the tip and ring points from the local unit match the tip and ring points of the remote.

zhoneHdsl2FrameSyncWord.name: zhoneHdsl2FrameSyncWord
zhoneHdsl2FrameSyncWord.description: A 10 bit number indicating the frame sync word used. LSB justified

zhoneHdsl2StuffBits.name: zhoneHdsl2StuffBits
zhoneHdsl2StuffBits.description: A 4 bit number for the stuff bits. LSB justified.

zhoneDslPerfDataTable.name: zhoneDslPerfDataTable
zhoneDslPerfDataTable.description: This table provides one row for each modem interface.

zhoneDslPerfLofs.name: zhoneDslPerfLofs
zhoneDslPerfLofs.description: Count of the number of Loss of Framing failures since agent reset.

zhoneDslPerfLoss.name: zhoneDslPerfLoss
zhoneDslPerfLoss.description: Count of the number of Loss of Signal failures since agent reset.

zhoneDslPerfLols.name: zhoneDslPerfLols
zhoneDslPerfLols.description: Count of the number of Loss of Link failures since agent reset.

zhoneDslPerfInits.name: zhoneDslPerfInits
zhoneDslPerfInits.description: Count of the line initialization attempts since agent reset. Includes both successful and failed attempts.

zhoneDslPerfCur15MinTimeElapsed.name: zhoneDslPerfCur15MinTimeElapsed
zhoneDslPerfCur15MinTimeElapsed.description: The number of seconds elapsed since the start of the current measurement period.

zhoneDslPerfCur15MinLofs.name: zhoneDslPerfCur15MinLofs
zhoneDslPerfCur15MinLofs.description: Count of the number of Loss of Framing failures in the current 15 minute interval.

zhoneDslPerfCur15MinLoss.name: zhoneDslPerfCur15MinLoss
zhoneDslPerfCur15MinLoss.description: Count of seconds in the current 15 minute interval when there was a Loss of Signal.

zhoneDslPerfCur15MinLols.name: zhoneDslPerfCur15MinLols
zhoneDslPerfCur15MinLols.description: Count of seconds in the current 15 minute interval when there was of Loss of Link.

zhoneDslPerfCur15MinInits.name: zhoneDslPerfCur15MinInits
zhoneDslPerfCur15MinInits.description: Count of the line initialization attempts in the current 15 minute interval. Includes both successful and failed attempts.

zhoneDslAlarmProfileTable.name: zhoneDslAlarmProfileTable
zhoneDslAlarmProfileTable.description: This table contains information for Alarm conditions. One entry in this table reflects a profile defined by a manager which can be used to define alarm conditions for a modem.

zhoneDslAlarmProfileEntry.name: zhoneDslAlarmProfileEntry
zhoneDslAlarmProfileEntry.description: An entry in the zhoneDslAlarmProfile Table.

zhoneDslAlarmProfileName.name: zhoneDslAlarmProfileName
zhoneDslAlarmProfileName.description: Configuration profile name. Used by the zhoneDslLineConfigProfile entry to map zhoneDslLine Entry to the appropriate profile. When `dynamic' profiles are implemented, the profile name is user specified. Also, the system will always provide a default profile whose name is `DEFVAL'. When `static' profiles are implemented, there is an one-to-one relationship between each line and its profile. In which case, the profile name will need to algorithmically represent the Line's ifIndex. Therefore, the profile's name is a decimal zed string of the ifIndex that is fixed-length (i.e., 10) with leading zero(s). For example, the profile name for ifIndex which equals '15' will be '0000000015'.

zhoneDslThreshold15MinLoss.name: zhoneDslThreshold15MinLoss
zhoneDslThreshold15MinLoss.description: The number of Loss of signal seconds on a DSL interface within any given 15 minutes performance data collection period, which causes the SNMP agent to send a TRAP. 0 will disable the trap.

zhoneDslThreshold15MinLols.name: zhoneDslThreshold15MinLols
zhoneDslThreshold15MinLols.description: The number of Loss of link seconds on a DSL interface within any given 15 minutes performance data collection period, which causes the SNMP agent to send a TRAP. 0 will disable the trap.

zhoneDslThreshold15MinLofs.name: zhoneDslThreshold15MinLofs
zhoneDslThreshold15MinLofs.description: The number of Loss of framing seconds on a DSL interface within any given 15 minutes performance data collection period, which causes the SNMP agent to send a TRAP. 0 will disable the trap.
